        "title": "Add Discord channel continuity plugin",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a generic channel context supplement/message observer seam to the plugin SDK.\n- Add the bundled `discord-channel-continuity` plugin with scoped Discord guild-channel buffering, CLI commands, config, docs, and tests.\n- Wire Discord inbound processing to prepend bounded same-channel context and record eligible channel messages, while skipping duplicates already present in the current inbound body.\n\nRefs #94750.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/channels/continuity/context-supplements.test.ts src/plugins/api-builder.channel-context.test.ts src/plugins/registry.channel-context.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-subpaths.test.ts extensions/discord-channel-continuity/src/config.test.ts extensions/discord-channel-continuity/src/store.test.ts extensions/discord-channel-continuity/src/format.test.ts extensions/discord-channel-continuity/src/supplement.test.ts extensions/discord-channel-continuity/src/cli.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/message-handler.process.test.ts`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:surface:check`\n- `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts`\n- `pnpm lint:extensions:no-src-outside-plugin-sdk && pnpm lint:extensions:no-relative-outside-package && pnpm lint:plugins:plugin-sdk-subpaths-exported`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nKnown proof gap: full `pnpm build` was attempted twice in this container and failed in `tsdown` with Node heap OOM around the detected ~3.3 GB heap cap, including a retry with `NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=8192`. The narrower SDK declaration/build-surface checks above pass.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Discord guild-channel messages can be buffered by account/guild/channel and recovered through a bounded plugin supplement when the normal inbound context lacks that same-channel text.\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout with Vitest project shards and plugin SDK checks.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm test ...message-handler.process.test.ts`, `pnpm plugin-sdk:surface:check`, `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts`, boundary/export lints, docs checks, and `git diff --check` as listed above.\nEvidence after fix: Focused tests passed 6 Vitest shards with 147 tests total; SDK surface reported public callable exports at budget (`5171`) and package-exported forbidden subpaths `0`.\nObserved result after fix: The Discord process test confirms registered same-channel supplements are prepended for guild messages and not called for DMs; the plugin supplement test confirms current/newer/cross-scope messages and already-present entries are skipped.\nWhat was not tested: A live Discord gateway restart/reset against a real guild channel, and full `pnpm build` due local `tsdown` OOM.\n",
